  ## Install oVirt using package manager

  **oVirt 4.2** is intended for production use and is available for the following platforms:

  - Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7.4 or later
  - CentOS Linux 7.4 or later
  - Scientific Linux 7.4 or later

  Our recommended method of installing oVirt is to use the pre-built packages for a supported Enterprise Linux 7 distribution,
  such as CentOS Linux or Red Hat Enterprise Linux. This makes installing oVirt very easy.

  {:.alert.alert-warning.col-md-6}
  **Important:** Please note you can not skip a version. If you are updating from e.g. 3.6, you first need to update to 4.0, then to 4.1 and finally to 4.2.
  If you're upgrading from a previous version, please update ovirt-release41 and verify
  you have the correct repositories enabled by running the following commands before upgrading with the usual procedure.
  <br/>
  ```
  # yum install http://resources.ovirt.org/pub/yum-repo/ovirt-release42.rpm
  ```
  <br/><br/>
  You should also read the [Release Notes for oVirt 4.2.0.](/release/4.2.0/)

